      "summary": "Europe continues to face a significant challenge with noise pollution, as over 20% of its population is exposed to harmful levels, particularly from persistent traffic noise. Despite existing frameworks, recent reports and calls from the European Parliament highlight the ineffectiveness of current EU noise directives and advocate for stronger action and better enforcement of legal limits, including those related to rest times and specific venues. There is also increasing EU-level attention on specific areas such as historical mandatory limits on underwater noise pollution and addressing cross-border issues like truck noise. A new EU report further underscores the urgent need for more robust measures to mitigate this pervasive environmental hazard across the continent.",
